{
  "texts": [
    "It has been found empirically that the same hyperparameter values lead to the best performances for both models.",
    "Since the hyperparameters do not look to be dependent on the origin of the training set, the same hyperparameter values were used across all models and their values are given in Supplementary Table 6.",
    "32 the AbNa-tiV models are trained to minimize a negative evidence lower bound (NELBO) consisting of three terms as follows:",
    "The first term is the negative log-likelihood reconstruction loss, which is characteristic of the VAEs.",
    "This term is approximated by the reconstruction m.s.e."
  ]
}